[878.977852, "i", "cat << 'EOF'\n\n========================================\nFINAL VERIFICATION SUMMARY\n========================================\n\nTask: Re-implement COBOL program in Python\n\nFiles Created:\n  - /app/program.py (5918 bytes)\n\nOriginal State Preserved:\n  - /app/src/INPUT.DAT (15 bytes) - unchanged\n  - /app/src/program.cbl (5762 bytes) - unchanged\n  - /app/data/ACCOUNTS.DAT (102 bytes) - unchanged\n  - /app/data/BOOKS.DAT (84 bytes) - unchanged\n  - /app/data/TRANSACTIONS.DAT (66 bytes) - unchanged\n\nFunctionality Verified:\n  ✓ Validation failure case: Both programs output identical message\n  ✓ Successful transaction case: Both programs produce identical data files\n  ✓ All three data files match byte-by-byte after successful transaction\n  ✓ Python program handles COBOL's unsigned arithmetic correctly\n  ✓ Python program reads short INPUT.DAT file correctly (15 bytes instead of 22)\n\nKey Implementation Details:\n  - Handles PIC 9(10) unsigned arithmetic (drops minus sign for negative values)\n  - Correctly interprets "]
[878.978084, "i", "\"200\" in 3-byte field as \"2000000000\" in 10-byte numeric field\n  - Validates buyer, seller, and book ownership before processing\n  - Updates account balances, book ownership, and transaction log\n  - Matches COBOL output format exactly\n\n========================================\n\nEOF\n"]
